    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's interesting. you mentioned the \"structural limitations\" and the veto power making it paralyzed. do historians see those as just natural hurdles in diplomacy, or do they actually argue that the whole UN framework is fundamentally broken and needs to be replaced by something else?",
      "source": "evaluator"
